<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4" color="#990000"><b>What else to read</b></font><p>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><i>Village Voice </i>senior editor Wayne Barrett's <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&amp;location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FRudy-Investigative-Biography-Rudolph-Guiliani%2Fdp%2F0465005241%3Fie%3DUTF8%26s%3Dbooks%26qid%3D1178429218%26sr%3D8-1&amp;tag=socialistwork-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325" target="_blank">Rudy! An Investigative Biography</a> </i>is packed with dirt about Giuliani--how he doctored statistics, backpedaled on key issues and caved to political cronies, all the while maintaining a fa&ccedil;ade of integrity and honesty.<p>
The excellent documentary <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&amp;location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGiuliani-Time-David-Dinkins%2Fdp%2FB000I8NGAK%3Fie%3DUTF8%26s%3Ddvd%26qid%3D1178429088%26sr%3D8-1&amp;tag=socialistwork-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325" target="_blank">Giuliani Time</a>, </i>directed by Kevin Keating, exposes the stories behind the "new" New York that Giuliani laid claim to. The film is now available on DVD.<p>
For more facts about the "war on crime" in Giuliani's New York and beyond, see Keeanga-Yamahtta Taylor's <a href="http://www.isreview.org/issues/32/racism.shtml" target="_blank">"Civil Rights and Civil Wrongs: Racism in America Today,"</a> published in the <i>International Socialist Review</i>. Another ISR article by Hadas Their, <a href="http://www.isreview.org/issues/46/nytransit.shtml" target="_blank">"A glimpse of union power,"</a> details Giuliani's attacks on city unions as the backdrop to the December 2005 New York transit strike.
